{
  "task_summary": "Given a list of integers, remove duplicates while preserving first occurrence order",
  "approach": "We can use a dictionary to track the indices of the unique elements we've seen so far. If we encounter an element that has already been seen, we can skip it by continuing to the next iteration. If not, we add it to our result list and update the dictionary.",
  "code": "```python\nimport json\n\ndef remove_duplicates(nums):\n    unique_indices = {}\n    result = []\n\n    for i, num in enumerate(nums):\n        if num not in unique_indices:\n            result.append(num)\n            unique_indices[num] = i\n\n    return json.dumps(result, indent=4)\n```",
  "complexity": {
    "time": "O(n log n)",
    "space": "O(n)"
  },
  "edge_cases": [
