  "approach": "To convert an integer to its binary representation, we can use the bitwise AND operator (&) and left shift (<<) operators. We start with the number 1 and repeatedly check if the input number is divisible by 2. If it is, we append a '1' to the result string; otherwise, we append a '0'. We then right-shift the input number by 1 bit.",
  "code": "def convert_to_binary(num: int) -> str:\n    if num == 0:\n        return '0'\n\n    binary = ''\n    while num > 0:\n        binary += '1' if num & 1 else '0'\n        num >>= 1\n\n    return binary[::-1]",
